title: CATER 154872, Kly Mod 22-3: WVGC fault.
text: Kly Mod 22-3: WVGC meter showed lo limit fault (< E-10). Energized filament numerous times to get vacuum up to 3.4 X E-8 and remain there. Suspect something may be wrong with gauge.

title: MFX 18 keV, 14-14.47 GeV
text: MFX requests 18 keV to start. This is would nominally be 14.47 GeV. My quick and dirty math has us at about 10.12 GeV available in L3. To have a couple spares (and not overshoot needing STDZ) suggest starting from the healthy 2mJ config for 9.8 keV. Then sneak up on the energy starting w/ 14.0 GeV. At 14.0 GeV, K is still a healthy 2.44. If there's just a ton of head room, can maybe creep up to 14.2 GeV. But prefer having 2 tubes worth to spare going into the 5 days delivery to MFX.

title: Kly Mod 21-3: lots of "rice krispies".
text: While riding by sector 21, noticed 21-3 had particularly active "rice krispies" from pulse xformer tank. Ranged thyratron from 4.4 volts to 5 volts where high limiting began. Still had lots of lobing on backswing of BV waveform, but it did settle down quite a bit. Left res volts @ 4.8. Thyratron was installed August 2021.

title: * Re: CATER 154872, Kly Mod 22-3: WVGC fault.
text: Checked WVGC readback: still at 1.4 X E-8 and station on.

title: Kly Mod 11-8: attempted restart of station, but klystron vacuum has OP fault.
text: Inspected station wiring to make sure everything is hooked up. Made sure ground hooks off. Checked pulse cable connections. Energized mod front panel 120 breakers and started filament time in. Energized KMB--MKSU shows klystron vac + mag current fault. Kly vac controller needle well above high limit (OP). Doesn't look like this will clear. Shut off KMB, trim supply breaker, and mod front panel breakers. Will have to have someone look into the klystron vac issue.

title: * Re: RTBSA having some issues - and crashing sometimes when you hit stop
text: Found that it's pretty laggy while trying to look at UNDH sepoints. I'm inclined to think this is an issue when trying to acquire data at 10Hz. We found that we can get UNDS setpoints VS GMD data fine at 110Hz. It would be interesting to see how RTBSA works at HXR 10/SXR 00 or HXR 00/SXR 10 beam rates.

title: * Re: Gun faulted on peak power interlock - tried to reset with these steps, but 10-2 not coming back on, leaving off

After this, tried these instructions, and was able to reset the peak power interlock fault, but now the RF switch says Off. Going to leave this off and let day shift address it.

title: Interesting factoid about all these RFS FS faults tonight (1/30/22 owl shift)
text: Something I think I learned tonight that I didn't know before... For most Cu LINAC stations, when a KCS flow switch faults, it turned of the station via the MKSU directly (WKL status). For the stations in 20-22, which have "upgraded" klystron focus, this setup appears to be significantly different... It appears that the KCS flow switch for these stations instead trips off the focus supply for the station, which leaves behind a focus fault (EMC) at the station, sort of indirectly turning off the station (inhibits SCR triggers to the modulator). These fault latch up in the focus control PLC, and once the flow switch fault returns to normal, a "reset all" command on the focus control EPICS recovers the EMC fault allowing the station to start firing again. I wish I had understood this two days ago... If anyone has better information than what I describe above, please enlighten me and any others who might have a stake in this game.
